    <string id="0">
        <![CDATA[Bolts of lightning arc across the passage in front of you! You jump back before you get baked.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="1">
        <![CDATA[Suddenly, huge, red creatures appear all around you!]]>
    </string>
    <string id="2">
        <![CDATA[Click.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="3">
        <![CDATA[What a disappointment. You've come all this way, only to finally reach an empty case.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="4">
        <![CDATA[The case only contains one item. It's an ancient scroll, over ten long. It is covered with faint, fine writing, painted on thin leather. Rolled up, it's almost six inches in diameter.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="5">
        <![CDATA[You unroll it slightly to look at it. It's not magical. It's more a work of history. It contains many small portraits of dragons, with pieces of biographical information.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="6">
        <![CDATA[It doesn't look too interesting to you. Someone, however, might find it very valuable. The key question is how much the lich Morog will mind your stealing it from her.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="10">
        <![CDATA[When you take the scroll, you hear a distant rumbling. The ground vibrates slightly under your feet. Someone isn't reacting well to your theft.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="11">
        <![CDATA[The pedestal bears a massive spell book. It's a monster - over eight inches thick, with a cover of dragon skin and spells painted on the pages with gold paint. It's an incredible piece of work.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="12">
        <![CDATA[This spell book must be Morog's. Only a creature as powerful and magical as a lich could own a magical tome this formidable.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="17">
        <![CDATA[The moment you touch the book, icy numbness races up your arm, spreads across your torso, and flows down your legs. You try to pull yourself away, only to find your hand stuck to the page!]]>
    </string>
    <string id="18">
        <![CDATA[Finally, with a last desperate bit of strength, you manage to throw yourself away from the book. You collapse to the ground, your skin frigid from head to toe.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="19">
        <![CDATA[You find a slender tome with a very simple alchemical recipe inside. You now know how to make Resurrection Balm.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="20">
        <![CDATA[This concealed bookshelf contains Morog's more esoteric and obscure magical tomes. Very few of them are of use to you, being dedicated to the more bizarre areas of magic.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="21">
        <![CDATA[One spell book, however, proves itself worth a quick browse. The spell inside is demanding, but not difficult to learn. You can now cast the spell Word of Recall.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="22">
        <![CDATA[This is the body of a Slithzerikai, recently killed and bled. The corpse is lying here, ready to provide a tasty meal for Morog.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="23">
        <![CDATA[Morog's Castle is more accomodating than you thought. This section contains a small town! This is a huge chamber, with a ceiling 40 feet high. Built inside it are several small shops, all of which are open for business.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="24">
        <![CDATA[Morog must keep this here to service the magical travelers who pass through the run, and the beings who come to her to deal or to buy assistance.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="25">
        <![CDATA[At first, this looks like a completely ordinary chair. Then you look closer, and see that it is covered with a network of tiny runes, etched all over its surface. It also has straps, designed to hold a reluctant person down.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="26">
        <![CDATA[Finally, you find traces of blood. Someone didn't wipe the chair down as well at they could have.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="31">
        <![CDATA[When you sit in the transmuting chair, the runes that cover every inch of its surface begin to glow. The powerful magic of the chair begins to transmute you into a sheep. Unfortunately, there are still a few bugs in the system.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="32">
        <![CDATA[You are spared a humiliating life as a sheep. The chair only hunches you over a bit, and makes tufts of wool spring on on your skin. The shock of the change also, incidentally, kills you.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="33">
        <![CDATA[This room is filled with dozens of small piles of bones. They are the mortal remains of all manner of creatures, some humanoids, some animals. All of the bones show signs of sharp teeth gnawing on them.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="34">
        <![CDATA[You stand at the entrance to Morog's throne room. She has constructed a magnificent palace, with this enormous, gleaming marble hall as its centerpiece.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="35">
        <![CDATA[The throne room was constructed over a natural caldera. Bubbling pits of hot mud keep the room intensely hot, and the sulphurous steam makes you faint. The ceiling glows, keeping the chamber well lit.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="36">
        <![CDATA[To the south, you see a massive throne. A small, hunched over, skeletal shape sits in it. Even though it looks ridiculously small sitting in the huge chair, you can feel the creature's power from here.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="37">
        <![CDATA[The being is a lich, one of the most powerful and feared beings in existence. Fortunately, it doesn't seem inclined to attack you. Yet.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="40">
        <![CDATA[Morog is a graceful host to her guests, but her hospitality has limits. Your theft of the history scroll was one of them. The moment you enter, the alarm is raised.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="41">
        <![CDATA[You have achieved the near-impossible - you have slain a lich. Morog literally falls apart. The magical force holding her bones together gone, they fall apart, and quickly molder into dust.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="42">
        <![CDATA[The portal is dim now. It's gotten much weaker. You're sure it's not strong enough to take you back down to the deep caverns. There's nothing else to do here.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="43">
        <![CDATA[This magical portal is different from the others scattered around this castle. It's larger and hotter, and has more power running through it. It looks more likely to send you far away from the Za-Khazi Run than across the building.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="49">
        <![CDATA[At first, you think you've made a critical mistake. The moment you step into the portal, you feel agonizing pain, as if you're being savagely ripped apart and the pieces are being carelessly tossed away.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="50">
        <![CDATA[Instead, you fall out of another portal, into a pitch black cavern. It's icy cold, and you feel as if the air is pressing in upon you. It feels as if you've been sent far, far away, possibly straight down.]]>
    </string>
</town>
